If not prevented by unforeseen circumstances, dear Mr Shillinglaw, I will be happy to attend at the Bateman-ceremony;



      The ceremony was the unveiling of a memorial to John Batman, held on Saturday 3 June 1882. The bound volume of materials relating to the memorial includes many other replies to the invitation to attend that are dated 31 May or 1, 2 or 3 June.
 but you know yourself, that in a public Department we are never quite masters of our time.
